<span id="freeTextContainer10396792835119915125">In the second book of the Father Tim series, Father Tim is returning from a summer in Sligo. Upon his return he sees that he really has not missed much as far the life in Mitford goes. <br/><br/>Father Tim meets Edith Mallory, a very wealthy widow, who is trying to catch him with her wonderful cooking ability. But, Father TIm is only interested in Cynthia, his neighbor.<br/><br/>Add to this mix, his cousin Meg who decides to move into the rectory and again Father Tim finds himself pastoring others. But, instead of </span>
  <span id="freeText10396792835119915125" style="display:none">In the second book of the Father Tim series, Father Tim is returning from a summer in Sligo. Upon his return he sees that he really has not missed much as far the life in Mitford goes. <br /><br />Father Tim meets Edith Mallory, a very wealthy widow, who is trying to catch him with her wonderful cooking ability. But, Father TIm is only interested in Cynthia, his neighbor.<br /><br />Add to this mix, his cousin Meg who decides to move into the rectory and again Father Tim finds himself pastoring others. But, instead of pastoring to meet their needs, he is now pastoring to meet his own needs.<br /><br />The story of Dooley and his struggles also continues.<br /><br />If you are still hooked on the series then don't hesitate to read "These High Green Hills" which is number 3 in the series.<br /><br /></span>
