        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer66858977" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10427214844789587552">Father Tim is the rector of Mitford, a small town packed with personality. The recently widowed Edith Mallory has got her sights set on him, confirmed bachelor that he is, as her next conquest. Meanwhile, his attempts at a relationship with his lovely neighbor Cynthia seem to be slowly gaining ground. And that&apos;s just his personal life! He&apos;s got his 12-year-old foster child, Dooley, to look after, a church building project, parishioners to counsel, and of course, the weekly sermon to write. <br/><br/>Karon</span>
  <span id="freeText10427214844789587552" style="display:none">Father Tim is the rector of Mitford, a small town packed with personality. The recently widowed Edith Mallory has got her sights set on him, confirmed bachelor that he is, as her next conquest. Meanwhile, his attempts at a relationship with his lovely neighbor Cynthia seem to be slowly gaining ground. And that's just his personal life! He's got his 12-year-old foster child, Dooley, to look after, a church building project, parishioners to counsel, and of course, the weekly sermon to write. <br /><br />Karon's style reminds me of L.M. Montgomery's Anne books: heartwarming stories of everyday people facing the problems of their lives with hope and humor. </span>
